text: Pyatiletka () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Nadezhdinsky Selsoviet, Iglinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 238 as of 2010. == Geography == It is located 45 km from Iglino. == References == Category:Rural localities in Iglinsky District
title: Pyatiletka, Nadezhdinsky Selsoviet, Iglinsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan
